result.execSummary:
The defendant Anthony J Hangartner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Anthony J Hangartner in court with attorney Martin J Lipske.  Matthew J Tingstad appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA calls case at 2:00 p.m.  Cites appearances.  Paul Samardich present and Samantha Hedican from DOC present.  Court acknowledges review of Revocation packet.  DA recommends 8 months and states reasons for sentence recommendation.  Atty Lipske requests 90-day jail sentence.  Defendant addresses the Court.  DA agrees with 72 days credit.  Atty Lipske states there may be more credit.  Court sentences def to 6 months with 72 days credit.  Good Time, no Huber.  If atty Lipske provides proof of more credit, clerk will amend JOC.  Adj.  klr
